The paper discusses the impact of noise on compressed sensing, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the effect of noise on the signal-to-noise ratio, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper briefly studies the setting where the signal is subject to random noise prior to measurement, which is a topic related to statistics (cs.SI).
